headline: Home Depot's prices to stay put despite tariffs, sales beats estimates
summary: (Reuters) -Home Depot said on Tuesday it will keep prices unchanged despite U.S. tariffs, after resilient demand from professional contractors helped the home-improvement chain beat first-quarter sales estimates and maintain its annual forecast.  The company was moving quickly to ensure that in the next 12 months, no single country outside the U.S. "will represent more than 10% of our purchases", CFO Richard McPhail said in a statement.  Home Depot's partnerships with suppliers and a diversified supply chain strategy will help it "generally maintain current pricing levels across its portfolio", he said.
